This paper focuses on visual prediction and control tasks, which are commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques, such as image processing and deep learning, which fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for fast adaptation, which involves learning from experience, and utilizes machine learning techniques, such as neural networks, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on real-world control tasks, which are often studied in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
